Welcome to the seventh version of samuelkillermann.com. At least &ndash; I think that's right. One thing I'm sure of: it's been a linear path of &ldquo;Each one is better than the last.&rdquo;
Sometimes embarrassingly better. If you're curious about what the old versions of this site looked like, by all means step into the Wayback Machine and take a tour. Don't say I didn't warn you.
So let's talk about what I've got going on here.

I co-created the Sexualitree model with friend / sex educator / curriculum writer extraordinaire Karen Rayne. We put our heads together to help sex educators introduce a popular concept to students: &ldquo;comprehensive sexuality education.&rdquo;
From the About page:
&ldquo;The Sexualitree is a way to see how we experience sexuality in different ways. Sexuality affects us on different levels of our lives, and each person uniquely.&rdquo;
We've created supplemental materials to help educators use the model, and it's been implemented in dozens of curricula.
